  "description": {
    "en": "A powerful and ferocious animal that resembles a small bear but is actually the largest land-dwelling weasel.",
    "zh": "一种强大而凶猛的动物，外表像小熊，但实际上是体型最大的陆生鼬科动物。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Wolverines are stocky, muscular animals weighing 9 to 25 kilograms, about the size of a medium dog. They have thick, dark brown fur with lighter stripes along their sides and a broad, rounded head with strong jaws. Their large paws spread wide like snowshoes, helping them move easily through deep snow.",
      "zh": "狼獾是粗壮而肌肉发达的动物，体重9到25公斤，大约有一只中型犬那么大。它们有厚厚的深棕色毛皮，体侧有较浅的条纹，头部宽而圆，下颌强壮有力。它们的大脚掌像雪鞋一样张开，帮助它们在深雪中轻松移动。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Wolverines are fierce and fearless, sometimes driving bears and mountain lions away from their food. They eat a variety of foods including carrion, small mammals, birds, and berries. They are solitary animals that roam enormous territories, sometimes traveling 24 kilometers in a single day to find food.",
      "zh": "狼獾凶猛无畏，有时会把熊和美洲狮从它们的食物旁边赶走。它们吃各种食物，包括腐肉、小型哺乳动物、鸟类和浆果。它们是独居动物，活动领地非常广阔，有时一天内会走24公里来寻找食物。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Wolverines live in cold, remote boreal forests, alpine tundra, and mountain regions of the Northern Hemisphere. In North America, they are found mainly in Alaska, northern Canada, and parts of the northern Rocky Mountains. They need large areas of wilderness with persistent snow cover and are very sensitive to human disturbance.",
      "zh": "狼獾生活在北半球寒冷偏远的北方针叶林、高山苔原和山区。在北美洲，它们主要分布在阿拉斯加、加拿大北部和北落基山脉的部分地区。它们需要大面积有持续积雪覆盖的荒野，对人类的干扰非常敏感。"
    }
  },
